'''Mikele ("Miki") Ronisse Barber''' (born October 4, 1980 in [[Livingston, New Jersey]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[Sprint (running)|sprinter]] who won gold at the [[4 x 100 m]]eters relay event in [[2007 World Championships in Athletics]], in [[Osaka, Japan]], and an individual gold medal at the [[100 meters]] in [[2007 Pan Am Games]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]].

She is the twin sister of [[Me'Lisa Barber]], who has also won relay medals on the world stage.
Recently qualified for the World Championships in Degu South Korea

