<ref>{{iaaf name|199570}}</ref>

==Bobsledding==
In October 2012, Bartoletta was named to the U.S. National [[bobsled]] team.<ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |title=US national bobsled team named |url=http://www.teamusa.org/USA-Bobsled-and-Skeleton-Federation/Features/2012/October/25/US-national-bobsled-team-named.aspx |publisher=Team USA.org |accessdate=October 26, 2012}}</ref> Bartoletta was one of three track and field Olympians (along with [[Lolo Jones]] and [[Hyleas Fountain]]) invited to the U.S. women's bobsled push championship by coach Todd Hays. Jones and Bartoletta made the bobsled team, giving them a chance to earn a spot on the bobsled World Cup circuit.<ref name=bostonbobsled>{{cite news |url=http://www.boston.com/sports/other-sports/2012/10/25/lolo-jones-selected-bobsled-team/hzn1IUNQpU6olKB6DJuWRO/story.html |title=Lolo Jones selected to US bobsled team |last=Reynolds |first=Tim |date=October 25, 2012 |agency=Associated Press |page= |accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> On November 9, 2012, Bartoletta and teammate [[Elana Meyers]] placed third in Bartoletta's first career World Cup bobsledding competition.<ref name=1stworldcup>{{cite news |url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/olympics/2012/11/09/lolo-jones-team-win-silver-in-wcup-bobsled/1694729/ |title=Lolo Jones' team win silver in World Cup bobsled |last= |first= |date=November 9, 2012 |agency=Associated Press |page= |accessdate=November 9, 2012}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Tianna Madison married John Bartoletta in 2012 and began going by her married surname after the Olympics that year. They reside near Tampa, Florida. She credits John for reviving her athletic career.<ref>[http://www.tampabay.com/sports/olympics/tampa-based-olympian-went-from-rags-to-riches-to-win-gold-love/2110120 Tampa-based Olympian went from rags to riches to win gold, love] Tampa Bay Times (March 21, 2013). Retrieved on 2016-08-20.</ref>

In the lead-up to the 2012 Olympics, Tianna publicly claimed to have had an abusive childhood and other problems with her parents. They ended up suing her and her husband for [[defamation]] in September.<ref>[http://chronicle.northcoastnow.com/news/2012/09/08/Tianna-Madison-parents-at-odds.html Tianna Madison, parents at odds] The Chronicle (September 8, 2012). Retrieved on 2016-08-20.</ref> However, they dismissed the lawsuit in March 2013.<ref>[http://www.morningjournal.com/general-news/20130319/defamation-lawsuit-against-tianna-madison-dismissed-by-her-parents Defamation lawsuit against Tianna Madison dismissed by her parents]. Morningjournal.com (March 19, 2013). Retrieved on 2016-08-20.</ref>

==Organization==
Bartoletta is the founder and president of Club 360, a program helping young women build successful lives by enabling them to broaden their experiences and make educated decisions.

