'''Jeanette Bolden''' (born January 26, 1960 in [[Los Angeles, California]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] [[Athletics (sport)|athlete]] who formerly competed in the 100 metres. She is currently the head coach of the [[UCF Knights track and field|track and field team]] at the [[University of Central Florida]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.orlandosentinel.com/sports/blogs/knights-notepad/os-ucf-ucf-hires-hall-of-fame-coach-jeanette-bolden-to-lead-track-team-20130626,0,5435237.post |title=UCF hires Hall of Fame coach Jeanette Bolden to lead track team |work=Orlando Sentinel |date=2013-06-26 |accessdate=2013-06-26}}</ref>

==World class sprinter==
She competed for the United States in the [[1984 Summer Olympics]] held in [[Los Angeles]], [[United States|U.S.]] in the 4 x 100 metres where she won the gold medal with her team mates 100 metre silver medalist [[Alice Brown (athlete)|Alice Brown]], [[Chandra Cheeseborough]] and Olympic 100m champion [[Evelyn Ashford]]. She also placed 4th in the [[100 metres]] in a time of 11.25 seconds.

Bolden has suffered from [[asthma]] throughout her life.  Her athletic career came to a sudden end at the 1988 [[United States Olympic Trials (track and field)|Olympic Trials]] when she ruptured her [[Achilles tendon]] just moments after teammate [[Florence Griffith Joyner]] set the still standing World Record in the 100 metres.<ref>http://www.usatf.org/statistics/champions/OlympicTrials/HistoryOfTheOlympicTrials.pdf Olympic Trials</ref>  It was one of the most heartbreaking memories for her coach [[Bob Kersee]].

==Assistant coach==
Unable to run with the same intensity as before, she applied her efforts to coaching, initially as an assistant coach at [[UCLA]] under Kersee.<ref>http://www.thefreelibrary.com/TRACK+COACH+FACES+THE+HURDLES+OF+ASTHMA.(LA.COM)-a0182294705 The Daily Breeze by Emily Henry</ref> Between 1994 & 2012, Coach Bolden has developed over 50 [[UCLA]] [[NCAA]] All-Americans in the sprints, hurdles and relays.<ref>http://www.uclabruins.com/ViewArticle.dbml?DB_OEM_ID=30500&ATCLID=207914495</ref>

==Head coach==
Bolden is currently head track and field coach for [[UCF]]  after a successful tenure with  [[UCLA]]'s women's program.<ref>http://www.usatf.org/news/view.aspx?DUID=USATF_2007_03_15_13_12_38 USATF</ref>  In 2008, she served as the United States Olympic women's head coach.<ref>http://www.usatf.org/news/view.aspx?DUID=USATF_2008_07_14_09_52_13 USATF Press Release</ref>

