'''Regina Jacobs''' (born August 28, 1963 in [[Los Angeles]]) is an [[United States|American]] former [[middle-distance runner]] from [[Los Angeles]]. She currently works as a real estate agent in Oakland, California with Bay Sotheby's International Realty<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sothebysrealty.com/eng/associate/180-a-932-4012723/regina-jacobs|website=BSIR}}</ref>.

==Track & field career==
After graduating from [[Stanford University]], Jacobs represented the USA in three consecutive [[Summer Olympics]], starting in [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988]] in [[Seoul, South Korea]].<ref name="si">{{cite web|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/2003/writers/mike_fish/11/25/hamilton/|title=Second guessing|last=Fish|first=Mike|date=November 25, 2003|work=SI.com|accessdate=2009-02-03}}</ref>

Jacobs took second place in the 1500 m race at the [[1997 World Championships in Athletics|6th World Championships in Athletics]] in [[Athens]] (4:04.63) in 1997, and again won the silver medal in the 1500 m at the World Championships in [[Sevilla]] in 1999 (4:00.35). In her years of running she won 25 national titles. On February 1, 2003, at age 39 Jacobs set a world record in the indoor 1500 m with a time of 3:59.98, becoming the first woman to break 4 minutes in the event.<ref>http://branchsportstech.com/2014_Meets/indoor/02-21-USATF/Result-Track.php?EN=5&RN=1&ST=Official&D=3#tab3</ref> Jacobs remains the only American woman to run under 4 minutes in the indoor 1500 meters and stands as the USATF American Indoor record holder in 2015. Regina's 2 mile record was broken by [[Jennifer Simpson]] in 2015.

In 2003 she retired after she tested positive for [[Bay Area Laboratory Co-operative|BALCO]]'s 'designer' steroid [[Tetrahydrogestrinone|THG]] and was suspended from competing in track & field for four years by the [[United States Anti-Doping Agency]].

==Real Estate Career==

Following her ban and subsequent retirement, Jacobs became a real estate agent in the [[Oakland, California|Oakland]], California area.  She currently works for Sotheby's International Realty.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sothebysrealty.com/eng/associate/180-a-932-4012723/regina-jacobs|title=Regina Jacobs Real Estate Associate in Oakland California - Sotheby's International Realty|website=www.sothebysrealty.com|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref>

